        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 3:22PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 321 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an outflow boundary along
a line extending from 7 miles east of Hot Springs State Park to 12
miles southwest of Thermopolis. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph. An isolated gust up to 60 mph
is possible.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Boysen State Park around 325 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

To report severe weather, contact your nearest law enforcement
agency. They will relay your report to the National Weather Service
office in Riverton.</instruction>
